works.description: This astonishing piece of valuable treasure from the Atocha shipwreck site in Florida Keys is the latest in the array of treasures that have been found here. A crew member discovered a 10-carat emerald and gold ring that is valued $500,000. People at the Atocha shipwreck site are lucky enough to find hidden or lost treasure ever since they found this ring along with two silver spoons two other silver-encrusted artifacts. The discovery spot is about 35-miles west of Key West within 300 feet of the sea where a gold rosary and gold bar were found in April.The ring was found by the salvagers crew of Mel Fisher’s Treasures while searching for the Nuestra Senora de Atocha, a Spanish sterncastle lost in the 1600s.
